3. A custom manager or additional nullable relation may be adding the outer join; inspecting the generated queryset/model will identify it.
4. The test fixture may leave a nullable relation unexpectedly absent, but changing fixture data would only mask the production-valid null case and is therefore the least likely/correct option.

I’ll test hypothesis 1 first and continue without waiting, as AFK mode requires.
